<dl id="n01011c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01011c">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01011c"> 11(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Brown Betty ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n01011c"> <li>FW prototext </li><li><ms href="#n01011c">MS BL 47471b-77v</ms> </li><li>JJA 48:010 <a name="h1B0d" href="../../ff/fdra/hda.htm#h1B0d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/h/h1B0d.htm#n01011c">Draft: I.8&sect;1B.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<mark>BROWN BETTY</mark>.]</font> Butter a deep pie-dish, and place a layer of finely chopped apples on the bottom. Cover with a layer of fine bread crumbs, sprinkle with sugar, and spice and small bits of broken-up butter. Then add another layer of apple, and cover as before, and so on till the dish is full. <small> <a name="IT30oct22" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT30oct22"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (30 October 1922) 2/5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
